The streets are said to be paved with gold, and the gates are made of pearls. The walls of the city are adorned with precious stones, and there is no need for a sun or moon, as the glory of God illuminates everything. The Bible also describes heaven as a place of worship and adoration. The angels and saints are constantly praising God, singing hymns of praise and offering their worship.
